The paper deals with the problem of committing transactions while enforcing a predefined order, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes algorithms that deploy a specialized cooperative transaction execution model, which involves coordination between multiple threads or processes, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed algorithms in micro benchmarks and various applications, which suggests that cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper provides the design and implementation of the proposed algorithms, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
